    shortAnswer: `Calculate expansion revenue by summing the additional recurring revenue from existing customers in a period through upsell, cross-sell, and seat or usage growth, excluding new customers. For example, 40 accounts each adding 2,000 dollars of ARR is 80,000 dollars of expansion. Track it as a share of new ARR to gauge your growth engine.`,
